					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7062035#post-3919477</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7062035/scp-4545#post-3919477</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 21 Aug 2018 00:12:41 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Jacob Conwell</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1372582</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>My dude, your picture is the Trojan Horse from 2004's <a href="https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0332452/">Troy</a>. Granted its a good picture, it's still funny to recognize it right off the bat</p> <p>That said there is a lot of charm to this article. Trojan horses popping up and spewing out smaller horses decked out in Greek armor like some kind of twisted Matryoshka doll brings a smile to my face. To be honest, this does a lot more with a historical concept in a lot fewer words than a bunch of the 4K entries did.</p> <p>+1. Solid work, Mortos.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
